                            <comment id="138285" author="niu" created="Fri, 8 Jan 2016 03:38:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Andreas, the displayed features including mmp is from MDS, but not OSS. That test seems doesn&apos;t have the debug patch included.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I found one failure which has debug patch included, &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_logs/d3a29f9e-b4be-11e5-8114-5254006e85c2/show_text&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_logs/d3a29f9e-b4be-11e5-8114-5254006e85c2/show_text&lt;/a&gt; , I think the script checking the mmp feature by looking at the failover_HOST variable isn&apos;t reliable (seems the variable could be exported even if no failover being used), I&apos;m going to change it to looking at the features on device directly.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="138239" author="adilger" created="Thu, 7 Jan 2016 19:06:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looking at the most recent test failure &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/56d8d2dc-b502-11e5-8114-5254006e85c2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/56d8d2dc-b502-11e5-8114-5254006e85c2&lt;/a&gt; it seems that MMP is enabled but the check is missing this feature?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
